label.value: normal protein localization to cell-cell contact point during mating

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the region of contact between two cells undergoing conjugation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal vegetative growth on papuamide B

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing papuamide B.

label.value: normal growth on papuamide B during mating

value.value: A phenotype in which cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing papuamide B when cells in the population are undergoing conjugation.

label.value: sensitive to papuamide B during vegetative growth

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to papuamide B. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of papuamide B that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to myriocin during mating

value.value: A phenotype in which cells show increased sensitivity to myriocin during mating. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of myriocin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal vegetative growth on myriocin

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing myriocin.

label.value: abolished protein export from nucleus during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein export from the nucleus does not occur during a cellular response to hydroxyurea. Export of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abolished during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein level during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydroxyurea is higher than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to ionizing radiation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to ionizing radiation is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydroxyurea is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: decreased protein level during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to hydroxyurea is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. label.value: normal protein localization to telomere during meiosis

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the telomere of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, elongated multiseptate cell with fragmented nucleus

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is elongated, has more than one septum and a nucleus that is broken into multiple small fragments, and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division.

label.value: inviable elongated cell with fragmented nucleus and mitotic cell cycle arrest in interphase

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable and elongated, has a nucleus that is broken into multiple small fragments, and progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in interphase. The cell contains no septum.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: decreased protein degradation during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of protein degradation is decreased during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein degradation during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of protein degradation is increased during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein degradation during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of protein degradation is increased during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased centromeric outer repeat transcript-derived siRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which small interfering RNA transcripts derived from the centromere outer repeat region are present at lower levels than normal.

definition.value: This term refers specifically to siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of RNA from the centromere outer repeat region. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences.

label.value: decreased spliced cen-dg RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which spliced forms of RNAs transcribed from dg repeats in the centromere outer repeat region are present at lower levels than normal.

label.value: increased calcium import

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of calcium ions into a cell occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased mature snRNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of mature snRNA measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased mature snRNA level

label.value: abnormal histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K4 specific)

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of H3-K4 specific histone methyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: abolished histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K4 specific)

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which H3-K4 specific histone methyltransferase activity is absent.

label.value: mitotic spindle elongation without chromosome separation with centromeric DNA dissociated from spindle

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic spindle elongation begins, but mitotic sister chromatid segregation stops before completing separation of chromosomes, DNA remains in a single mass at or near the midpoint of the mitotic spindle, and centromeric DNA is not closely associated with the mitotic spindle.

label.value: mitotic spindle elongation without chromosome separation with centromeric DNA associated with spindle

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic spindle elongation begins, but mitotic sister chromatid segregation stops before completing separation of chromosomes, DNA remains in a single mass at or near the midpoint of the mitotic spindle, and centromeric DNA is closely associated with the mitotic spindle.

label.value: decreased protein localization to kinetochore during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is decreased during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal attachment of mitotic spindle microtubules to kinetochore

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the physical attachment of sister chromatids to mitotic spindle microtubules is abnormal.

definition.value: This term is less specific than 'abnormal mitotic sister chromatid biorientation' (FYPO:0000326) because sister chromatid biorientation normally occurs only as part of metaphase plate congression, not during other stages of mitosis. FYPO:0004213 can be used for abnormal attachment observed at any time during mitosis.

label.value: normal protein localization to kinetochore during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal histone H4-K20 methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is abnormal.

label.value: abolished histone H4-K20 monomethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which monomethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 does not occur.

label.value: abolished histone H4-K20 dimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 does not occur.

label.value: abolished histone H4-K20 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 does not occur.

label.value: normal histone H4-K20 methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H4-K20 monomethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which monomethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H4-K20 dimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H4-K20 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased histone H4-K20 monomethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which monomethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased histone H4-K20 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 20 of histone H4 occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abnormal nucleosome binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of nucleosome binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is abnormal. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with a nucleosome that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished nucleosome binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which nucleosome binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased nucleosome binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of nucleosome binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to UV

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to ultraviolet light.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal growth during cellular response to ionizing radiation

value.value: A cell population growth phenotype in which vegetative cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) during a cellular response to ionizing radiation.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during cellular response to UV

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to ultraviolet light.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
